THS the Albanese government’s social media age restrictions

The Albanese government's social media age restrictions will come into effect in December this year. They will require social media companies to take reasonable steps to prevent Australians under the age of 16 from registering accounts on their platforms. These restrictions will apply to Facebook, TikTok and YouTube, among other platforms.

THW Send Their Child with Moderate Autism to a Disabled School

Disabled schools are institutions where all students have a specific disability, and the curriculum is fully tailored to meet their unique learning needs. In contrast, educational support units exist within mainstream schools and provide specialised teachers and adapted curricula while allowing students to participate in regular classes and school activities alongside their peers. Moderate autism is a form of autism spectrum disorder where a child may have noticeable difficulties with social communication, repetitive behaviors, and adapting to change.

THR the emphasis on voting for political parties rather than focusing on the individual in Sri Lanka

Sri Lanka's Election Commission was recently being recognized as the best in the world. However, Sri Lanka's political system has been dominated by legacy parties since independence. Some parties represent singular ideologies while others offer mixed platforms; some are classified by religious and cultural lines. Voters have predominantly followed a party-based system in state and provincial elections, prioritizing party affiliation over individual candidates.

THW breakup

You are a 17 year old Sri Lankan Christian teenage girl and You have entered into a relationship with a Muslim boy with whom you have shared a long-term emotional connection. Both of you have developed strong mutual feelings and care deeply for one another. However, the relationship has to be kept private due to his parents’ disapproval, which stems from differences in your religious backgrounds. This situation has created ongoing challenges, including limited opportunities for communication and meeting in person. Although you had initially hoped that these restrictions would ease over time, the circumstances have remained largely unchanged, causing emotional strain and uncertainty for both parties.
